line_1: It did not argufy my playing.
line_2: I've done, she mutter'd — I was saying,

line_1: And on his bench apart the fiddler playing,
line_2: Where dogs and children through the crowd are straying,

line_1: Or on beds of roses playing,
When all was Riot, Masking, Playing;
line_2: I hid this Coin, when Charles was swaying;

line_1: And talk all at once, while the Music is playing:
line_2: For they come to the Pump, as before I was saying,

line_1: Count the bees that on Hybla are playing,
line_2: Count the flocks that on Tempe are straying,

line_1: Should we miss but a tree where we us'd to be playing,
line_2: Or find the wood cut where we saunter'd a-Maying, —
